All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ArrivalEvent
Represents a specific type of event when a customer arrives at the store.
CheckOutQueue
Represents a checkout queue in the store.
EnterEvent
Represents a specific type of event when a customer enters the store.
Event
Serves as the base class for all events within the simulation, encapsulating the common functionalities and properties that every event must have.
EventQueue
Manages a queue of events for the simulation, handling the scheduling, execution, and dynamic insertion of events based on their scheduled time.
ExponentialRandomStream
Generates random numbers following an exponential distribution.
K
 
LeaveEvent
Represents an event where a customer leaves the store after completing their payment.
MakeAllCustomers
Generates all customers for the store simulation based on exponential distribution to model inter-arrival times.
MakeCustomer
Represents an individual customer within the store simulation.
Optimize
Optimizes the checkout process in a store simulation to minimize the number of missed customers.
PayEvent
Represents an event where a customer pays for their items at the checkout.
PickEvent
Represents an event where a customer finishes picking items and is ready to join the queue for checkout.
QueueEvent
Represents an event where a customer either joins a queue for checkout or proceeds directly to payment if a checkout is immediately available.
RunSim
Entry point class for running the store simulation.
Simulator
Orchestrates the execution of the store simulation, initializing the simulation environment, generating customers, scheduling their arrival events, and processing events through the event queue.
State
Provides a foundational abstraction for managing the state of the simulation.
StoreState
Represents the state of the store during the simulation, including time management, customer queue management, and keeping track of various statistics such as missed customers, paid customers, and total queue time.
StoreView
Acts as the observer view for the store simulation, responsible for displaying progress, parameters, and results.
UniformRandomStream
Generates random numbers following a uniform distribution within a specified range.
View
Abstract class that implements an observer.
